\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \tab Paul stood at the stove in the dark kitchen, heating a skillet.  As he stirred the bowl of pancake batter he replayed the conversation he and Rebekkah had shared, pulling up the corners of it, looking for hidden meaning.  }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \tab There had been a few dozen people in the hallway at the time - socializing, rummaging through lockers . . . but she had come directly to him.  }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \tab She had seemed - not desperate.  Genuine, maybe.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \tab \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Hey, how\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s it going?\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  she had said, a friendly bounce in her voice.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \tab \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Gooood.\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  Paul had replied, confused.  The greeting was just familiar enough to make him question whether he had been mistaken for someone else.  }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \tab \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Sorry, I don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t think we really know eachother - I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 m Rebekkah!  Didn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t we have, like, Spanish together or something?\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0 }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \tab \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Ah, I don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t know, maybe.\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0   They definitely had.  He had spent a considerable ammount of time pretending not to be starring at her and her friends - a grouping of four or five similarly attractive girls in the back corner of the classroom.  He was pretty sure they had caught on eventually, had started facing away from him intentionally to show that his surveilance was not appreciated.  If he\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d ever said anything, to any of them, maybe the admiration would have come off a little more endearing, or maybe he would feel less inclined to stare, having finally made verbal contact with them but - that had been the year before, and he was glad that, at least superficially, any previous encounters had been scrubbed from the record.  }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \tab \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Well, we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re planting a garden in the lot behind the cafeteria over the summer.  Anything we grow is going to be donated to the food pantry downtown.  A-S-S-U-M-I-N-G we actually grow anything, which is hard to say at this point, have you seen the back patio?  I know they\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re still in the middle of clearing it but its really hard to imagine anything growing there right now!\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0 }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \tab \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Yeah,\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  Paul bobbed his head along to the syncopation of the conversation.  He was so focused on remaining an active participant that he found it hard to hear what she was saying.  }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \tab \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Aaaaanyway,\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  she continued, swaying slowly from foot to foot, \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Eight to three, lunch provided.  Though, you could totally bring a snack or something, I think we're just bringing PB&Js, and those little bags of chips?  Probably koolaid or something, I'm not sure.  Sooo yeah, maybe I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll see ya there?\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0 }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \tab \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Yeah, maybe!\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0   Paul funneled the anxiety into a sort of feigned excitement - happy, but noncommital.  }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \tab \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Ok great!\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0   And with this she smiled, pivoted, and walked away as casually as she had approached.}
